load ../infoflow-confidentiality.maude

--- Delegation context theta: operator > bankRole and operator > emailRole, so
--- operator acts-for both compartments, while bankRole and emailRole are
--- INCOMPARABLE. public acts-for no one. Owners: bank data readable by bankRole,
--- email data readable by emailRole.

--- Coverage: INCOMPARABLE compartments. Bank-owned secret reaching an
--- email-cleared sink leaks, because emailRole does not act-for bankRole. A
--- single global lattice cannot express this; the partial order can.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, emailRole)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: a too-low party. Bank-owned secret reaching a public sink leaks;
--- public does not act-for bankRole.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, public)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: join box. b3 carries both bank and email secrets; reaching a
--- bank-cleared sink leaks on the email token, because bankRole does not act-for
--- emailRole. Mixing two compartments exceeds either single-compartment reader.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  secretSource(b2, emailRole) readAuth(emailRole, emailRole)
  flow(b1, b3) flow(b2, b3) egressSink(b3, bankRole)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: declassifying one path does not sanitize the source for its OTHER
--- uses. b1 is declassified to public into b2, but b1 also flows raw into b3
--- which reaches a public sink. The raw second path still leaks.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  declassify(b1, b2, bankRole) flow(b1, b3) egressSink(b3, public)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Bite: a higher authority reads everything. Bank secret reaching an operator
--- sink is safe; operator acts-for bankRole. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, operator)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the cleared compartment reads its own. Bank secret to a bankRole sink is
--- safe; bankRole acts-for bankRole (reflexive).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, bankRole)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the core property. Bank secret reaching a public sink THROUGH a
--- declassify is safe; the released projection carries no secret.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, bankRole) readAuth(bankRole, bankRole)
  declassify(b1, b2, bankRole) egressSink(b2, public)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the other compartment. Email secret reaching an operator sink is safe;
--- operator acts-for emailRole too.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-CONFIDENTIALITY :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole))
  secretSource(b1, emailRole) readAuth(emailRole, emailRole)
  flow(b1, b2) egressSink(b2, operator)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .
